It's a really solid port, runs incredibly well. The training mode is directly from the Neo Geo AES, which means very basic options which doesn't include some of the more modern features training modes have, but is still pretty helpful and very welcome. The added controller support is a wonderful addition for those who want to take the game a bit more seriously and have more precision with their control. The one major feature the game is lacking is online versus, but the netcode probably wouldn't have been that solid anyways so bluetooth versus is nice. Also has some graphic options including aspect ratio for those who don't want the borders and scanlines to imitate an old CRT, which look pretty nice.   For the lack of currently common training mode options (which I wasn't expecting and honestly what is there is fine for most situations) and the lack of online versus I give it a 4 instead of a 5, but this is absolutely worth owning if you're interested in 98 on the go, probably the definitive mobile version and absolutely ranks up there in home versions of the game.
